  "texts": [
    "To measure the correlation between citation counts c i,t and quality q i at time step t we used the Pearson correlation coefficient.",
    "To measure citation churn at time step t, we used the number of papers cited in time t that were not cited in time t-1.",
    "Larger values represent more churn.",
    "To measure citation inequality at time step t, we utilized the Gini coefficient of citation distribution in time t, computed by dividing the area between the equal cumulative distribution of citations and the actual cumulative distribution of citations by the area under the curve of the equal cumulative distribution.",
    "Larger values represent more inequality.In sum, we build a set of agent-based models based on how people read and cite empirically, measure how turning rhetorical citing on and off affects three relatively measurable and muchdiscussed metrics of community health-the correlation between Perceived quality s i,j,t [0,2] See the section \"Methods\" (Eq. ( 2))."
